                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Townsend</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 16, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Hay informs Mr. Townsend that the Government of the United States desires
                    China’s neutrality to be respected everywhere as far as practicable in a state
                    of war which must, of course, be carried on in part on the waters or soil of
                    China, but to make a general agreement of the powers possible this Government
                    can not specify metes and bounds. Our general view has been accepted by nearly
                    all the powers, and their representatives at St. Petersburg, Peking, and Tokyo
                    are being instructed in that sense.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
